IaC (Infrastructure as Code) is the process of managing and provisioning infrastructure (servers, networks, databases, cloud resources, 
etc.) using code instead of manually creating them through a UI.

Interview:
Infrastructure as Code (IaC) is the practice of provisioning and managing infrastructure using code and automation tools instead of manual
processes.

Example Without IaC

Manually creating:

EC2 instance
Security groups
VPC
Load balancer

through AWS Console step-by-step.

Example With IaC

Using a tool like:

Terraform
AWS CloudFormation
Ansible

to write code such as:

resource "aws_instance" "web" {
  ami           = "ami-12345"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
}
Then run one command:
terraform apply

and infrastructure is created automatically.

Benefits of IaC
Automation
Faster deployments
Consistency
Version control with Git
Easy recovery/recreation
Reduced human error

Popular               IaC Tools
Tool	                Purpose
Terraform	            Cloud infrastructure provisioning
AWS CloudFormation	  AWS infrastructure automation
Ansible	              Configuration management & automation
Pulumi	              IaC using programming languages

Why IaC matters? Why is it used?

Terraform is used to automate the creation and management of infrastructure such as:

EC2 instances
VPCs
Security groups
Load balancers
Databases
Kubernetes clusters

using code.

Benefits of Terraform:

Automation → Creates infrastructure automatically
Consistency → Same setup every time
Version Control → Infrastructure code can be stored in GitHub
Multi-Cloud Support → Works with AWS, Azure, GCP, etc.
Faster Deployment → Infrastructure created in minutes
Reduced Human Errors → Avoids manual configuration mistakes
Reusable Code → Same templates can be reused across projects

Terraform is used to automate infrastructure provisioning using code, making deployments faster, consistent, scalable, and less 
error-prone.
